deck: Colorist for Shinobi: Ninja Princess, and In the Blue. Artist and writer for Jackiea and the Red Ninja Clan.
description: Drawing since he was 13, Marvin has done a few works for some companies. At Maw Productions (www.toshigawa.com) he has colored Shinobi: Ninja Princess and In the Blue (a comic for the Anime Blues Con). Marvin has drawn a pin-up in the book Cupcakes and Cuties that was published from Broad Sword comics.
name: Marvin Cheveallier

deck: Jack Tremblay was a Canadian artist who drew for such comics as "Wow" and Triumph during the 40's.
description: Jack Tremblay created his character "Crash" Carson in 1942 when he was only 16 and still in high school, Bell buying this strips due to so many other artists and writers being called away during World War II.
name: Jack Tremblay
